title: Leave
tags: 
speaker: Caravan Master Odema
colorID: 0
position: 1776,-361
---
Hold on. Take someone with you. I know you're not some helpless tenderfoot - not like most of this lot. But you drop dead I don't wanna be looking for the body. Got a schedule to keep.

<em>He scans over the travelers, resting his eyes at length on a sturdy, armor-clad woman who has spent the journey's nights sleeping on uneven ground without blanket or pillow.</em>

[[Leave2]]
===
title: Leave2
tags: 
speaker: Caravan Master Odema
colorID: 0
position: 2072,-365
---
Calisca. Calisca!

<em>The woman looks up on her own time.</em>

[[Leave3]]
===
title: Leave3
tags: 
speaker: Caravan Master Odema
colorID: 0
position: 2359,-368
---
He needs to find some springberries. Whatch that he doesn't drop dead.

[[Leave4]]
===
title: Leave4
tags: 
speaker: Calisca
colorID: 0
position: 2653,-373
---
No promises.

[[Leave5]]
===
title: Leave5
tags: 
speaker: Caravan Master Odema
colorID: 0
position: 2964,-371
---
What kind of a guide says something like that?

[[Leave6]]
===
title: Leave6
tags: 
speaker: Calisca
colorID: 0
position: 3282,-366
---
Kind you can afford.

[[Leave7]]
===
title: Leave7
tags: 
speaker: Caravan Master Odema
colorID: 0
position: 3596,-370
---
<em>Odema chuckles and shakes his head. He looks at you.</em> Don't listen to her. You're in good hands.

<em>He casts a sidelong glance at her.</em> And I pay too well if anything.

[[Leave8]]
===
title: Leave8
tags: 
speaker: Caravan Master Odema
colorID: 0
position: 3886,-370
---
<em>Odema's small grin recedes beneath his mustache, and he is stern once more.</em>

Off with you. Heodan should have supplies. See that you're equipped before you head out. We're in harsh country.

Get your berries and hurry back. And if you get so much as a tickle of wind, you drop everything and you run. Something in the air tonight. If it's a bîawac, we'll shelter in the ruins, hut-dwellers be damned.
===
